  <div class="comment_text">Compression&#x2F;decompression is a good problem for proof of correctness. The specification is very simple (you must get back what you put in), while the implementation is complex.<p>What seems to have happened here is that the storage allocator underneath is unverified. That, too, has a relatively simple spec - all buffers disjoint, no lost buffers, no crashes.</div>
  
